### 4.7 Frontend Architecture

```
frontend/
├── app/
│   ├── page.tsx                    # Landing / session start
│   ├── session/[id]/page.tsx       # Active session with avatar
│   └── doctor/
│       ├── page.tsx                # Doctor dashboard
│       └── session/[id]/page.tsx   # Session review
├── components/
│   ├── SimliAvatar.tsx             # Simli WebRTC avatar component
│   ├── SessionControls.tsx         # Start/pause/end controls
│   ├── SessionTimer.tsx            # Duration tracking
│   └── TranscriptPanel.tsx         # Live transcript (optional)
└── lib/
    ├── pipecat-client.ts           # Pipecat WebRTC client setup
    └── api.ts                      # FastAPI client
```

**Session Page Flow:**
1. User clicks "Start Session" → Frontend calls `POST /api/sessions/start`
2. Backend creates session, spins up Pipecat pipeline, returns WebRTC room URL
3. Frontend connects to the Pipecat WebRTC transport (Daily or native WebRTC)
4. Simli avatar video + TTS audio stream to the browser
5. User's microphone audio streams to Pipecat → STT → LLM → TTS → Simli → back to browser
6. On "End Session" → Frontend calls `POST /api/sessions/{id}/end`, pipeline shuts down

