## 5. Real-Time Session Flow (Detailed)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User (Browser)
    participant F as Frontend
    participant PC as Pipecat Pipeline
    participant STT as Deepgram STT
    participant LLM as LangChain LLM
    participant TTS as ElevenLabs TTS
    participant SIM as Simli Avatar
    participant API as FastAPI
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    U->>F: Click "Start Session"
    F->>API: POST /sessions/start {script_id, patient_id}
    API->>DB: Create session record
    API->>PC: Spin up Pipecat pipeline
    PC-->>F: WebRTC room URL
    F->>PC: Connect WebRTC (audio+video)
    
    Note over PC,SIM: Avatar greets user with first question
    LLM->>TTS: "Hello! How are you feeling right now?"
    TTS->>SIM: Speech audio stream
    SIM->>PC: Lip-synced avatar video
    PC->>F: Avatar video + audio
    F->>U: Avatar speaks the question

    Note over U,PC: User responds
    U->>F: Speaks into microphone
    F->>PC: Audio stream (WebRTC)
    PC->>STT: Audio chunks (streaming)
    STT-->>PC: Interim transcripts
    STT->>PC: Final transcript: "I've been feeling stressed about work"
    
    PC->>LLM: {question, response, history}
    PC->>API: Save exchange + run sentiment
    API->>DB: Store Q&A exchange
    
    LLM->>PC: Action: ACKNOWLEDGE + "Thank you for sharing that..."
    LLM->>TTS: "Thank you for sharing that. What specifically about work has been weighing on you?"
    TTS->>SIM: Audio stream
    SIM->>PC: Avatar video
    PC->>F: Stream to browser
    F->>U: Avatar responds naturally

    Note over U,DB: Loop continues until script complete
    
    U->>F: Click "End Session"
    F->>API: POST /sessions/{id}/end
    API->>DB: Finalize session
    API->>PC: Shutdown pipeline
```

