## 7. Technology Stack Summary

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| **Frontend** | Next.js + React | Session UI + Doctor Dashboard |
| **Avatar** | Simli (via Pipecat plugin) | Lip-synced talking avatar |
| **Real-time Pipeline** | Pipecat | Frame-by-frame audio/video processing |
| **Transport** | WebRTC (Daily or native) | Real-time browser ↔ server communication |
| **STT** | Deepgram (streaming) | Real-time speech-to-text |
| **TTS** | ElevenLabs or Cartesia | Text-to-speech for avatar |
| **LLM** | GPT-4o via LangChain | Session brain — script following + sentiment |
| **VAD** | Silero (Pipecat built-in) | Voice activity detection for turn-taking |
| **Backend API** | FastAPI (Python) | REST API for sessions, scripts, doctor dashboard |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL | Session data, scripts, transcripts, sentiment |
| **ORM** | SQLAlchemy + Alembic | Database models + migrations |
| **Sentiment** | Custom (via LLM or lightweight model) | Emotion tracking per exchange |

---

## 8. MVP Scope (Phase 1)

For the prototype/demo, focus on:

- [x] **1 hardcoded script** with 5-6 questions
- [x] **Pipecat pipeline** with Deepgram STT + GPT-4o + Cartesia TTS + Simli avatar
- [x] **Basic session flow** — start session → avatar asks questions → user responds → avatar acknowledges → next question
- [x] **REASK logic** — if user response is unclear, gently re-ask
- [x] **Session storage** — save all Q&A exchanges to PostgreSQL
- [x] **Simple frontend** — session page with avatar, start/end buttons
- [x] **Basic doctor view** — read-only page showing session transcript

**Deferred to Phase 2:**
- Multiple scripts management UI
- Advanced sentiment analytics dashboard
- Patient management
- Session scheduling
- Multi-doctor support
- Distress alerts

